occurs in the Chapada dos Veadeiros region, in the municipality of Alto Paraíso de 
<collectingRegion box="[316,384,1940,1966]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="1" pageNumber="168">Goiás</collectingRegion>
, in the Brazilian state of 
<collectingRegion box="[663,728,1940,1966]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="1" pageNumber="168">Goiás</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation box="[744,812,1940,1966]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1184,1206]" captionTargetBox="[151,1429,222,1121]" captionTargetId="figure-28@4.[151,1436,222,1130]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Map showing the known distributionof Stachytarpheta flavovirescens P.H.Cardoso and Stachytarpheta salimenae P.H.Cardoso &amp; Menini in Brazil." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5585446" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5585446/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="168">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
