<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="171" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,1289,1963]" pageId="4" pageNumber="171">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,653,1289,1315]" pageId="4" pageNumber="171">Provisional conservation assessment—</emphasis>
Although the Chapada dos Veadeiros is intensively studied, only 
<specimenCount pageId="4" pageNumber="171" type="generic">three specimens</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[285,619,1325,1351]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Stachytarpheta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="171" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="flavovirescens">
<emphasis box="[285,619,1325,1351]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="171">Stachytarpheta flavovirescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were collected to date in 1993, 2005, and 2013. It seems that the populations are small and narrowly distributed. This species is only known from three localities, and shows an EOO of 
<quantity box="[1337,1443,1361,1388]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.051" pageId="4" pageNumber="171" unit="km" value="5.051">5.051 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[1443,1451,1361,1375]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="171">2</superScript>
and an AOO of 
<quantity box="[321,394,1397,1423]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="4" pageNumber="171" unit="km" value="12.0">12 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[394,402,1397,1411]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="171">2</superScript>
. Even though this species occurs within a protected area (i.e., Parque Nacional da Chapada dos Veadeiros), it is under multiple threats, including tourism, the expansion of agricultural and livestock activities, increased frequency of anthropogenic fires, and invasive exotic species, especially grasses (
<bibRefCitation author="Fiedler, N. C. &amp; Merlo, D. A. &amp; Medeiros, M. B. D." box="[1162,1372,1469,1495]" pageId="4" pageNumber="171" pagination="153 - 161" refId="ref5602" refString="Fiedler, N. C., Merlo, D. A. &amp; Medeiros, M. B. D. (2006) Ocorrencia de incendios florestais no Parque Nacional da Chapada dos Veadeiros, Goias. Ciencia Florestal 16: 153 - 161. https: // doi. org / 10.5902 / 198050981896" type="journal article" year="2006">
Fiedler 
<emphasis box="[1250,1306,1469,1495]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="171">et al.</emphasis>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Souza, C. D. D. &amp; Felfili, J. M." pageId="4" pageNumber="171" pagination="135 - 142" refId="ref6180" refString="Souza, C. D. D. &amp; Felfili, J. M. (2006) The utilization of medicinal plants in the region of Alto Paraiso of Goias, GO, Brazil. Acta Botanica Brasilica 20: 135 - 142. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0102 - 33062006000100013" type="journal article" year="2006">Souza &amp; Felfili 2006</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Barbosa, A. G." box="[310,468,1505,1531]" pageId="4" pageNumber="171" refId="ref5314" refString="Barbosa, A. G. (2008) As estrategias de conservacao da biodiversidade na Chapada dos Veadeiros: conflitos e oportunidades. Universidade de Brasilia, Brasilia, 128 pp." type="book" year="2008">Barbosa 2008</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Silva, M. S. &amp; Gurgel, H. &amp; Laques, A. &amp; Silveira, B. D. &amp; Siqueira, R. V." box="[479,604,1505,1531]" pageId="4" pageNumber="171" refId="ref6107" refString="Silva, M. S., Gurgel, H. Laques, A., Silveira, B. D. &amp; Siqueira, R. V. (2018) 30 anos de dinamica espacotemporal (1984 - 2015) da regiao de influencia do Parque Nacional da Chapada dos Veadeiros Goias. Revista franco-brasilera de geografia 35: http: // journals. openedition. org / confins / 14851" type="url" year="2018">Silva 2018</bibRefCitation>
). These threats have contributed to a decline of the species EOO, AOO, and habitat quality. Based on the criterion and sub-criteria B1ab (i, ii, iii) of the 
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN Standards &amp; Petitions Committee" box="[979,1132,1541,1567]" pageId="4" pageNumber="171" refId="ref5733" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Committee (2019) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 14. Available from: http: // www. iucnredlist. org / documents / RedListGuidelines. pdf (accessed 17 May 2021)" type="book" year="2019">IUCN (2019)</bibRefCitation>
, this species is provisionally considered as “CR” (Critically Endangered).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[189,1080,1613,1639]" pageId="4" pageNumber="171" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,1289,1963]" box="[189,1080,1613,1639]" pageId="4" pageNumber="171">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,356,1613,1639]" pageId="4" pageNumber="171">Etymology:—</emphasis>
The specific epithet refers to the yellow-greenish inflorescences.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="171" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,1289,1963]" pageId="4" pageNumber="171">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,428,1649,1675]" pageId="4" pageNumber="171">Taxonomic notes:—</emphasis>
Among the 
<taxonomicName box="[562,820,1649,1675]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Stachytarpheta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="171" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[562,732,1649,1675]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="171">Stachytarpheta</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
with atropurpureous to black corollas, 
<taxonomicName box="[1263,1451,1649,1675]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Stachytarpheta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="171" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="flavovirescens">
<emphasis box="[1263,1451,1649,1675]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="171">S. flavovirescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[340,437,1685,1711]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Stachytarpheta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="171" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mollis">
<emphasis box="[340,437,1685,1711]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="171">S. mollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is also endemic to the Chapada dos Veadeiros (Cardoso 
<emphasis box="[1163,1220,1685,1711]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="171">et al.</emphasis>
2020). Both species show hairy leaves, hairy bracts, hairy calyces, and congested, yellow-greenish inflorescences. However, they can be distinguished by the characters summarized in 
<tableCitation box="[661,745,1757,1783]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="5.[136,199,159,183]" captionTargetBox="[144,1435,231,1500]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Table 1. Morphological comparison of Stachytarpheta flavovirescens, S. salimenae, S. glazioviana, S. mollis, and S. sericea." pageId="4" pageNumber="171">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,1289,1963]" pageId="4" pageNumber="171">
<taxonomicName box="[189,528,1793,1819]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Stachytarpheta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="171" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="flavovirescens">
<emphasis box="[189,528,1793,1819]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="171">Stachytarpheta flavovirescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can also be confused with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Pohl) S. Atkins (2005: 230)" authorityName="S. Atkins" authorityPageNumber="230" authorityYear="2005" baseAuthorityName="Pohl" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Stachytarpheta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="171" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="longispicata" variety="longipedicellata">
<emphasis box="[851,1020,1793,1819]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="171">S. longispicata</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[1082,1264,1793,1819]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="171">longipedicellata</emphasis>
(Pohl) S. 
<bibRefCitation author="Atkins, S." pageId="4" pageNumber="171" pagination="161 - 272" refId="ref5224" refString="Atkins, S. (2005) The genus Stachytarpheta (Verbenaceae) in Brazil. Kew Bulletin 60 (2): 161 - 272." type="journal article" year="2005">Atkins (2005: 230)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
when fruiting due to the elongated inflorescences. Both species are found in the region of the Chapada dos Veadeiros (
<bibRefCitation author="Atkins, S." box="[313,460,1865,1892]" pageId="4" pageNumber="171" pagination="161 - 272" refId="ref5224" refString="Atkins, S. (2005) The genus Stachytarpheta (Verbenaceae) in Brazil. Kew Bulletin 60 (2): 161 - 272." type="journal article" year="2005">Atkins 2005</bibRefCitation>
), but can be separated by a series of morphological features. Namely, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="S. Atkins" authorityYear="2005" baseAuthorityName="Pohl" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Stachytarpheta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="171" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="longispicata" variety="longipedicellata">
<emphasis box="[1282,1451,1865,1891]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="171">S. longispicata</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[187,369,1901,1927]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="171">longipedicellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has pedicellate flowers laxly arranged along the rachis and salmon-colored corollas, while 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Stachytarpheta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="171" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="flavovirescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="171">S. flavovirescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has sessile flowers in a congested arrangement along the rachis, and atropurpureous to black corollas.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
